Tweet Content: "Starting in October, work to dismantle the Miniestadi will begin, and will last for six months. Once gone, the land will be used for the construction of the New Palau Blaugrana. https://t.co/wKh5QnDPQl"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "Unfortunately, life moves on for everyone and the games that had been played at the Miniestadi are being held this season at the new Johan Cruyff Stadium, which opened on August 27. Bar√ßa B, the U19, and the Women‚Äôs teams now have a new home adapted to the times. https://t.co/QfsOOcwFw0"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "During the last decade, the Miniestadi has continued to sell out for pivotal Bar√ßa B, U19, and Women‚Äôs matches. Especially noteworthy has been the success of the Women's team, which last April celebrated its first berth in the Champions League final. https://t.co/DpB0SntGiD"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "Recently, one of the biggest days of the year at the Miniestadi has been the traditional open training session before the Three Kings holiday. Thousands of children have had their dreams of seeing the Bar√ßa players up close come true. https://t.co/1xP7YNHDCV"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content:
"Not just footballers.

The Miniestadi also became great starting point for coaches, including the likes of Pep Guardiola and Luis Enrique, who after gaining promotion with Bar√ßa B would become the only Bar√ßa managers to win the treble. https://t.co/3huA4MMQek"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "Years later, those same players would hoist Bar√ßa‚Äôs second Champions League title in Paris. On that day, the Miniestadi packed in 11,000 fans who watched the final against Arsenal on a giant video screen. https://t.co/855K780fQ9"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "One of the most memorable occurred when Bar√ßa B, led by Puyol and Xavi, beat Real Madrid B 5-0 in the playoffs for promotion to the Second Division. https://t.co/Us6pHP57mn"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content:
"At the end of the 90's and after the turn of the century, the Mini bore witness to the emergence of players like Puyol, Xavi Hern√°ndez, Vald√©s, Iniesta, and Leo Messi, among many others.

With them on the field, Bar√ßa‚Äôs little coliseum would experience many unforgettable nights. https://t.co/IZUwEXP82S"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "In the summer of 1992, when Camp Nou was being used for the Olympics, the Miniestadi hosted the official presentation of the 1992/93 first team squad. The same happened again in 1994, while work was being carried out at Camp Nou. https://t.co/ZBSIMpR9Jt"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "During the 1980's and 1990's the Miniestadi hosted numerous world-class music concerts featuring the likes of Bob Dylan, Carlos Santana, Queen, David Bowie and Elton John. https://t.co/nI7uXcWo1I"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "First, however, the home of Bar√ßa B and other youth teams would fill up for the first time in the last 16 of the 1983/84 Copa del Rey. Bar√ßa Athletic (the former name of the Bar√ßa reserve team) hosted Real Madrid‚Äôs first team ... and drew 0-0!"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content:
"On that first day, the Miniestadi hosted stars like Maradona & Schuster, and a boy named Guillermo Amor, who would become one of the pillars of Cruyff's Dream Team.
It was just the beginning. The Miniestadi was about to witness the emergence of a unique generation of footballers https://t.co/ZgYuVvFXEN"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content: "Built by the architect Josep Casals and project manager Ramon Dom√®nech, the Miniestadi opened on September 23, 1982, after just nine months of construction. It had a capacity for 15,276, distributed in two levels, with a covered grandstand. https://t.co/1t4MctTH1y"
Name: "FC Barcelona"

Tweet Content:
